data.text:
Trunk Line

Norwegian railway line between Oslo and Eidsvoll

Distance: Approx. 218 meters

Latitude and longitude: 60.01861111,11.10083333

The Trunk Line (Norwegian: Hovedbanen) is a railway line in Norway which runs between Oslo and Eidsvoll.

Lundermoen

Village in Østlandet, Norway

Distance: Approx. 3273 meters

Latitude and longitude: 60.01416667,11.15861111

Lundermoen is a village in Lillestrøm municipality, Norway. Its population is 1,207.

Leirsund

Village in Østlandet, Norway

Distance: Approx. 1859 meters

Latitude and longitude: 60,11.1

Leirsund is a village in the municipality of Lillestrøm, Norway. Its population (2005) is 1,177, of which 83 people live within the border of the neighboring municipality Sørum.

Frogner, Akershus

Village in Østlandet, Norway

Distance: Approx. 943 meters

Latitude and longitude: 60.02333333,11.11055556

Frogner is a village in Sørum municipality, Norway. Its population is 1,174.

Skedsmokorset

Village in Østlandet, Norway

Distance: Approx. 3709 meters

Latitude and longitude: 60.01666667,11.03333333

Skedsmokorset is a village in the municipality of Lillestrøm and in the county of Akershus. Its population is approximately 15,000.

Lindeberg Station

Railway station in Lindeberg, Norway

Distance: Approx. 2974 meters

Latitude and longitude: 60.03944444,11.12805556

Lindeberg Station is a railway station located at Lindeberg in Sørum, Norway. The station is located on the Trunk Line and was opened in 1944. The station is served by Oslo Commuter Rail trains with hourly services from Dal Station to Oslo Central Station and Drammen Station.

Frogner Station

Railway station in Frogner, Norway

Distance: Approx. 698 meters

Latitude and longitude: 60.02277778,11.10305556

Frogner Station is a railway station at Frogner in Akershus, Norway on the Trunk Line. The station was opened in 1854 as part of the Trunk Line. It is served by twice-hourly service R13 by Vy.

Leirsund Station

Railway station in Skedsmo, Norway

Distance: Approx. 1996 meters

Latitude and longitude: 60,11.08694444

Leirsund Station is a railway station at Leirsund in Skedsmo, Norway on the Trunk Line. It is served by an hourly services, R13 by Vy. The station was opened in 1859, five years after the rest of Hovedbanen.
